    <p class="lead">If your coffee suddenly tastes dull, bitter, or a little like cardboard, your grinder is often the culprit. Old grounds hide in the chute and burr chamber, stale oils cling to the hopper, and all of that gets mixed right back into your fresh beans. The good news? A burr grinder is usually easy to clean once you stop overthinking it.</p>
